The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Wednesday, November 10, 2004

 Road to avoid

 SP Mukherjee Road. in front of Kalighat Metro station. Work on water pipes.

 Soiree

 A Hindustani classical sitar recital by Supratik Sengupta, accompanied by Gopal Mishra (tabla), at ITC Sangeet Research Academy, 6 pm. 

 Dance

 A workshop on Odissi dance, conducted by Ratikanta Mahapatra, at Savarmati Dance amp; Music Centre on Raja SC Mullick Road, between 10 am and 7 pm.

 Theatre

 Choopkatha will stage Mrs Soriano, directed by Dolly Basu, at Cluster 14, Purbachal, Salt Lake, 7 pm.

 Exhibition

 An exhibition of colonial furniture, affordable art and Northeast tribal handloom, organised by Innerspace, at 2/1, Loudon Street, 11 am to 7 pm. 

 Launch

 A book release function to mark the publication of Ghalib: Nirbachita Kabita at Sahitya Akademi, 5.30 pm. A reading session will follow.

 Art watch

 Artist A. Ramachandran will inaugurate Artspace India City Gallery at 7, Deodar Street, 4 pm. An exhibition, featuring ceramic works of muralist Tamal Bhattacharya, will also be opened.




